  "text": "Other limitations are that, although we considered selfprotection and cognitive deficits as explanations for PIB, the mechanisms behind these explanations (e.g., self-presentation desires or cognitive functioning) were not measured. In addition, whereas children with ADHD demonstrate explicit PIB in multiple domains (e.g., social, behavioral, academic, athletic; [CITATION_1] , this study only investigated social and behavioral PIB. Furthermore, although it is standard in the PIB literature for adult-informant reports to compose the external index of children's actual competence, this leaves open the possibility that adults may have inaccurately rated children's competence. Finally, the ADHD group was small, which prevented exploration of results by ADHD subtype or comorbidities (known to be associated with explicit PIB; [CITATION_2] .",
